{"body": "For my opinion the patch is good but I  think that in general we have not to consider all cases of reserved words, that are a normal thing in  many contexts of programming languages and frameworks \nMuch complex regular expressions  could be made ```render``` slow, also ```render partial: 'nav-dropdown-logged-in' ``` according to the ruby/rails convention convention should be ```render 'nav_dropdown_logged_in' ``` that not fails\nAlso in ruby you can't use ```-``` in the method name or in a symbol\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7258442", "created_at": "2012-07-25T18:57:53Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7129#issuecomment-7258442", "updated_at": "2012-07-25T18:57:53Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7129, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/acapilleri", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0cd98f4e263d306bc455ca750c31443f?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2e17b55bd1f302b773d04e4938adef85.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0cd98f4e263d306bc455ca750c31443f", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "acapilleri", "type": "User", "id": 46208, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/acapilleri/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ffa2bd3543c15100be79"}, "id": 7258442, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7129"}
